http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Simmering-resentment/article14017504.ece

The CITU took out a rally at Ranasthalam in the district opposing the establishment of Kovvada nuclear power plant.Members of the trade union alleged that both the Union and State governments were trying to disturb the lives of people by proposing the set up the plant in the district. CITU district general secretary D. Govinda Rao and others leaders raised slogans against the governments and said the project would be detrimental to the interests of workers too as they would be residing in the vicinity of the Kovvada area after the development of industrial zone in and around Pydibhimavaram.They vowed to extend support to people opposing the project though the government was promising good financial package for them.